// secrets.h.example  -  OPTIONAL one-time WiFi seed.
//
// WiFi is normally provisioned on-screen: the radio scans for networks and you
// type the password on the on-screen keyboard. The chosen credentials are saved
// to the board's NVS flash and reused automatically after every reboot.
//
// secrets.h is therefore OPTIONAL. If you want the board to come up already
// knowing your network on its very first boot (before any saved credentials
// exist), copy this file to secrets.h and fill it in:
//   cp secrets.h.example secrets.h
//
// secrets.h is gitignored so your real credentials are never committed. Delete
// it (or leave it absent) to rely purely on the on-screen setup.
//
// To change networks later: long-press the title bar to re-open WiFi setup.
#pragma once

#define WIFI_SSID "your-wifi-name"
#define WIFI_PASS "your-wifi-password"
